＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝

				Conventions

＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝＝

1. class names begin with an uppercase letter;
	ex: class Mail
2. fucntion names begin with a lowercase letter;
	ex: void goHome();
3. based on the above elements, capitalize first letter of the word follow-up;
4. name of constant uses uppercase letters;
	ex: #define BIRTHDAY 20110308
5. it should be a noun or a noun phrase for a class name;
	ex: class DreamMaker
6. it should be a verb for verb phrase for a function name;
	ex: bool makeMeHappy();
7. every bool variant should be looks like a sentence;
	ex: bool isTimeUp; bool hasCheckedOut = true;
8. external prefix would be added before an member param;
	ex: m_sourceList; _isEngaged;
9. static members under item 8: sm_sourceList; s_isEngaged;
10. function name for getters:
	bools : bool isEngaged();
	non-bools: char* getNewsHeader();
			   int newsHeader();
11. function name for setters:
	setSeedUrl(char* url);
12. comments: follow 'doxygen'




framework:
global.h -- global setting for structures
linerlistbase.h -- sequence list support
					problems with 'operator ='
linklistnodebases.h -- link list (includes simple linked list and double linked list node)
linklistbase.h -- double linked list
